On the 73rd birthday of the United States Air Force, the President expresses gratitude and celebrates the accomplishments of the world's most powerful flying force. The Air Force has played a crucial role in protecting the American people, advancing national interests globally, and ensuring the country's leadership in innovation and aviation. Throughout its history, the Air Force has achieved remarkable advancements, such as breaking the sound barrier, activating the Global Positioning System, and launching the first remotely piloted aircraft. The President acknowledges the Air Force's mission to defend American freedoms and highlights their contributions in combat operations, disaster relief, and the fight against the coronavirus. The Air Force's commitment to air superiority has been evident in all conflicts and missions, and the President honors all Airmen who serve and defend the nation. The President concludes by expressing gratitude to all service members and their families for their service and sacrifice.